    <div class="container">
        <h1>User Guide - Megacity Cab Service Admin Portal</h1>
        
        <div class="step">
            <h2>Step 1: Access the Admin Portal</h2>
            <p>Navigate to the admin portal. You will see a screen like this:</p>
            <img src="../assets/ss1.png" alt="Admin Portal Entry">
            <p>Click on <span class="highlight">"Get Admin Credentials"</span> if you are a new admin. If you already have an account, proceed to login.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="step">
            <h2>Step 2: Login to the Admin Dashboard</h2>
            <p>Enter your registered email and password in the login form:</p>
            <img src="../assets/ss3.png" alt="Login Screen">
            <p>Click the <span class="highlight">"Login"</span> button to access the dashboard.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="step">
            <h2>Step 3: Navigating the Dashboard</h2>
            <p>After logging in, you will see the admin dashboard:</p>
            <img src="../assets/ss4.png" alt="Admin Dashboard">
            <p>Here?s what you can do:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Manage drivers by clicking on <span class="highlight">"Manage Drivers"</span></li>
                <li>Handle vehicle records under <span class="highlight">"Manage Vehicles"</span></li>
                <li>Check customer details via <span class="highlight">"Customers"</span></li>
                <li>View and edit bookings in <span class="highlight">"Manage Bookings"</span></li>
                <li>Check billing information under <span class="highlight">"View Bills"</span></li>
                <li>Monitor financial transactions via <span class="highlight">"View Transactions"</span></li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        
        <div class="step">
            <h2>Step 4: Logging Out</h2>
            <p>Once you?re done, click <span class="highlight">"Logout"</span> on the sidebar to exit the system safely.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="step">
    <h2>Step 5: Managing Ride Requests</h2>
    <p>Navigate to the <span class="highlight">"Ride Requests"</span> section to view pending ride requests:</p>
    <img src="../assets/ss17.png" alt="Ride Requests">
    <p>Here, you can:</p>
    <ul>
        
        <li>Assign a driver to a requested ride.</li>
        <li>View ride details such as pickup and drop-off locations.</li>
    </ul>
</div>

<div class="step">
    <h2>Step 6: Monitoring Active Rides</h2>
    <p>Check the <span class="highlight">"Active Rides"</span> section to see ongoing trips:</p>
    <img src="../assets/ss13.png" alt="Active Rides">
    <p>This page allows you to:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>View driver and passenger details.</li>
        <li>Update the requests status.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
        
        <div class="step">
    <h2>Step 7: Managing Drivers</h2>
    <p>To manage drivers, navigate to the <span class="highlight">"Manage Drivers"</span> section from the sidebar. You will see a screen like this:</p>
    <img src="../assets/ss5.png" alt="Driver Management Page">
    <p>This page allows you to:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>View a list of all registered drivers.</li>
        <li>Check their availability status.</li>
        <li>Edit or delete driver records using the action buttons.</li>
        <li>Register a new driver by clicking the <span class="highlight">"Register New Driver"</span> button.</li>
    </ul>
</div>

<div class="step">
    <h2>Step 8: Registering a New Driver</h2>
    <p>Click the <span class="highlight">"Register New Driver"</span> button to open the registration form:</p>
    <img src="../assets/ss7.png" alt="Register New Driver Form">
    <p>Fill in the following details:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Full Name:</strong> Enter the driver's full name.</li>
        <li><strong>Email:</strong> Provide a valid email address.</li>
        <li><strong>Password:</strong> Set a secure password for the driver.</li>
        <li><strong>Phone Number:</strong> Enter the driver's contact number.</li>
        <li><strong>Address:</strong> Add the driver's residential address.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Once all details are filled in, click the <span class="highlight">"Register"</span> button to add the new driver to the system.</p>
</div>

<div class="step">
    <h2>Step 9: Editing or Deleting a Driver</h2>
    <p>On the <span class="highlight">"Manage Drivers"</span> page, each driver has two action buttons:</p>
    <img src="../assets/ss11.png" alt="">
    <ul>
        <li><span class="highlight">Edit</span>: Click the green edit button to update driver details.</li>
        <li><span class="highlight">Delete</span>: Click the red delete button to remove a driver.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Confirm the deletion before proceeding, as this action cannot be undone.</p>
</div>
<div class="container">  
    <h2>Step 10:Customer Management</h2>  

    <h2>Overview</h2>  
    <p>The Customer Management feature of the Megacity Cabs application allows users to efficiently manage customer data. This includes adding new customers, viewing existing customer details, and updating or deleting customer information as needed.</p>  

    <h2>Accessing the Customer Management Panel</h2>  
    <p><strong>Navigate to the Customers Section:</strong> From the main menu on the left side of the application, select <strong>Customers</strong>. This will direct you to the Customer Management interface.</p>  

    <h2>Key Features</h2> 
     <img src="../assets/ss10.png" alt="">
        <img src="../assets/ss12.png" alt="">

    <ul>  
        <li><strong>Customer List:</strong> Displays a comprehensive list of registered customers, including:  
            <ul>  
                <li><strong>Registration Number:</strong> Unique identifier for each customer.</li>  
                <li><strong>Name:</strong> Customer?s full name.</li>  
                <li><strong>NIC:</strong> National Identification Card number.</li>  
                <li><strong>Phone:</strong> Customer's contact number.</li>  
                <li><strong>Address:</strong> Physical address of the customer.</li>  
            </ul>  
        </li> 

        <li><strong>Register New Customer:</strong> Click on the <strong>Register New Customer</strong> button to open the registration form. Fill in the necessary details and submit to add a new customer to the database.</li>  
        <li><strong>Actions:</strong> Each customer entry includes two action buttons:  
            <ul>  
                <li><strong>Edit:</strong> Click to modify customer details. Update the fields as needed and save changes.</li>  
                <li><strong>Delete:</strong> Click to remove the customer from the database. A confirmation prompt will appear; confirm to proceed with deletion.</li>  
            </ul>  
        </li>  
    </ul>  
</div> 
        
        <div class="step">
            <h2>Step 11: Vehicle Management</h2>
            <h2>Overview</h2>
            <p>The Vehicle Management feature allows administrators to add, edit, and remove vehicles used in the cab service.</p>
            
            <h2>Accessing the Vehicle Management Panel</h2>
            <p>To manage vehicles, navigate to the <span class="highlight">"Manage Vehicles"</span> section in the sidebar.</p>
            <img src="../assets/ss8.png" alt="Vehicle Management Page">
            <p>This page allows you to:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>View a list of all registered vehicles.</li>
                <li>Check vehicle details including model, license plate, and assigned driver.</li>
                <li>Edit or delete vehicle records using the action buttons.</li>
                <li>Register a new vehicle by clicking the <span class="highlight">"Register New Vehicle"</span> button.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="step">
            <h2>Step 12: Registering a New Vehicle</h2>
            <p>Click the <span class="highlight">"Register New Vehicle"</span> button to open the registration form:</p>
            <img src="../assets/ss9.png" alt="Register New Vehicle Form">
            <p>Fill in the following details:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Vehicle Model:</strong> Enter the make and model of the vehicle.</li>
                <li><strong>License Plate:</strong> Provide the vehicle's license plate number.</li>
                <li><strong>Driver Assignment:</strong> Select the driver assigned to the vehicle (if applicable).</li>
                <li><strong>Status:</strong> Indicate whether the vehicle is active or under maintenance.</li>
            </ul>
            <p>Click the <span class="highlight">"Register"</span> button to add the new vehicle.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="step">
            <h2>Step 13: Editing or Deleting a Vehicle</h2>
            <p>On the <span class="highlight">"Manage Vehicles"</span> page, each vehicle has two action buttons:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><span class="highlight">Edit:</span> Click the green edit button to modify vehicle details.</li>
                <li><span class="highlight">Delete:</span> Click the red delete button to remove a vehicle from the system.</li>
            </ul>
            <p>Confirm the deletion before proceeding, as this action cannot be undone.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="step">
            <h2>Step 14: Managing Billing and Transactions</h2>
            <h2>Viewing Billing Records</h2>
            <p>To view billing records, navigate to the <span class="highlight">"View Bills"</span> section from the sidebar.</p>
            <img src="../assets/ss14.png" alt="Billing Records Page">
            <p>On this page, you can see a list of all generated bills, including:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Bill Number</li>
                <li>Customer Name</li>
                <li>Total Amount</li>
                <li>Status (Paid/Pending)</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        
        <div class="step">
            <h2>Updating Payment for a Bill</h2>
            <p>To update a payment, click the <span class="highlight">"Update Payment"</span> button next to the respective bill.</p>
            <img src="../assets/ss15.png" alt="Update Payment Button">
            <p>This action will take you to the <span class="highlight">New Payment Transaction</span> page.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="step">
            <h2>Creating a New Payment Transaction</h2>
            <p>On the <span class="highlight">New Payment Transaction</span> page, fill in the required details:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Payment Method:</strong> Choose from Cash, Credit Card, or Online Payment.</li>
                <li><strong>Amount Paid:</strong> Enter the amount the customer is paying.</li>
                <li><strong>Reference Number:</strong> (Optional) Add a reference for online transactions.</li>
            </ul>
            <p>Click the <span class="highlight">"Submit Payment"</span> button to complete the transaction.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="step">
            <h2>Viewing All Transactions for a Bill</h2>
            <p>Once a payment is made, you can view all related transactions by clicking on the <span class="highlight">"View Transactions"</span> button for that bill.</p>
            <img src="../assets/ss16.png" alt="View Transactions Page">
            <p>Here, you will find:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Transaction ID</li>
                <li>Payment Method</li>
                <li>Amount Paid</li>
                <li>Date of Payment</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
         <h2>Support</h2>  
    <p>For any technical issues or further assistance, please refer to the <strong>User Guide</strong> or contact the support team directly through the application.</p>  

 </div>
